# 20_warp_popover — substrate-layer suite for WarpPopover's full
# control set (s198 m2).
#
# Substrate-style test (per TESTING.md grandfather clause). Each
# sub-test proves the substrate contract holds — abbrev resolves,
# verbs dispatch, queries read back.
#
# Scope (s198 m2): all 5 widgets in WarpPopover.cpp migrated
# in a single pass — top/bot anchor SpinButtons, Preset DropDown,
# Quality Scale, Done Button. WarpPopover is a value-held member
# of MainWindow, so its ctor runs at app launch and all five
# substrate widgets are addressable without opening the popover.
#
# Architectural firsts banked by this milestone:
#   - First Scale substrate outside Toolbar.cpp (Toolbar had no
#     Scale; this is the first time the Scale substrate's
#     Adjustment-taking ctor proves out in a real call site).
#   - First DropDown substrate constructed with a runtime-populated
#     StringList (preset_names walk) where the contents are static
#     for the popover's lifetime — sits between Toolbar's anchor
#     dropdown (literal-list ctor) and the palette dropdown (runtime
#     model-swap). Validates that the StringList ctor path works
#     for "built once from data" lists.
#
# DSL note (carried from s196 m1 / s198 m1): the DSL lexer is
# kind-strict. SpinButton and Scale `value`/`min`/`max` queries
# return Double; round-number literals in asserts need explicit
# `.0` suffix.
#
# The tested abbrevs:
#
#   pop_wrp_tn    (top anchor count SpinButton — range 2..4)
#   pop_wrp_bn    (bot anchor count SpinButton — range 2..4)
#   pop_wrp_pr    (preset DropDown — 8 entries from preset_names())
#   pop_wrp_q     (quality Scale — range 1..16)
#   pop_wrp_done  (Done Button — popover dismissal)
#
# Test protocol:
#   1. Open the Scripter window.
#   2. Load this script.
#   3. Run. Every line should PASS.
#
# Side effects: every value written here also writes through to
# AppPreferences (the popover's on-change handlers are the same code
# path real user edits take). The test restores each control to a
# reasonable default at the end (top=2, bot=2, preset=0, quality=4)
# — these are NOT necessarily the user's previous values; they're
# the AppPreferences-installation defaults. Anyone running this
# test should expect their Warp defaults to be reset to the
# installation values.

#[sub] Top anchors SpinButton — min/max document the adjustment range.

assert pop_wrp_tn min == 2.0
assert pop_wrp_tn max == 4.0

#[sub] Top anchors SpinButton — set/value round-trip across the range.

pop_wrp_tn set 3.0
assert pop_wrp_tn value == 3.0
pop_wrp_tn set 4.0
assert pop_wrp_tn value == 4.0
pop_wrp_tn set 2.0
assert pop_wrp_tn value == 2.0

#[sub] Bottom anchors SpinButton — min/max document the adjustment range.

assert pop_wrp_bn min == 2.0
assert pop_wrp_bn max == 4.0

#[sub] Bottom anchors SpinButton — set/value round-trip across the range.

pop_wrp_bn set 3.0
assert pop_wrp_bn value == 3.0
pop_wrp_bn set 4.0
assert pop_wrp_bn value == 4.0
pop_wrp_bn set 2.0
assert pop_wrp_bn value == 2.0

#[sub] Preset DropDown — count matches PRESET_COUNT (8 entries from preset_names()).

assert pop_wrp_pr count == 8

#[sub] Preset DropDown — set/selected round-trip by index.

pop_wrp_pr set 0
assert pop_wrp_pr selected == 0
pop_wrp_pr set 3
assert pop_wrp_pr selected == 3
pop_wrp_pr set 7
assert pop_wrp_pr selected == 7
pop_wrp_pr set 0
assert pop_wrp_pr selected == 0

#[sub] Quality Scale — min/max document the adjustment range.

assert pop_wrp_q min == 1.0
assert pop_wrp_q max == 16.0

#[sub] Quality Scale — set/value round-trip.

pop_wrp_q set 8.0
assert pop_wrp_q value == 8.0
pop_wrp_q set 1.0
assert pop_wrp_q value == 1.0
pop_wrp_q set 16.0
assert pop_wrp_q value == 16.0
pop_wrp_q set 4.0
assert pop_wrp_q value == 4.0

#[sub] Done Button — label is "Done".

assert pop_wrp_done label == "Done"

#[sub] Done. 5 new substrate widgets in WarpPopover.cpp — full file
#[sub] migrated. First Scale substrate outside Toolbar.cpp lands here.
